    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="41"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <head>41. Telegram 345 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d41fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–855. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-08"
                            >August 8, 1955, 1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d41-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d41-1"/>
                <p>345. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Haguiwara asked me dinner Saturday night during which he outlined steps thus far
                    taken at Geneva enter into contact with CHICOMS on repatriation Japanese and
                    tried sound me out on raising level contacts. Spoke of government sending some
                    one to Peiping.</p>
                <p>I confined myself to general discussion present stage my talks, my hope
                    experience and possible result my talks would be helpful Japanese and suggested
                    question any further steps be taken by Japanese be discussed Tokyo or
                    Washington.</p>
                <p>He said no reply had yet been received from CHICOM Consul General here and
                    Tatsuke was again going to press for reply this week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Note: Advance copy to Mr. Waddell (FE) Noon 8-8-55 CWO/FED</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
